x4freetext: The experimental method.
The B-10, C-13, Zr-90 and Pb-208 targets were enriched
to greater than 96% abundance. All of the other targets
are either monoisotopic or nearly monoisotopic, in
which case the measyred cross sections are averaged
over the natural isotopic composition. The target
thicknesses, determined by weighing, were on the order
of 100 mg/cm**2.  All targets were elemental except
for N-14, O-16 and F-19, which were C(3)H(6)N(6) =
melamine, Li-O-H and C-F(2)=Teflon, respectively.
The N-14 and F-19 cross sections were corrected for the
carbon contribution, and the stability of the Li-O-H-
target was verified by heating in vacuum and
reweighing.
- By Compiler - The authors give beam energy above
threshold.  Beam energy in Laboratory Frame were
Calculated by Compiler.
Three 1.27-cm thick plastic Cerenkov counters.
One 0.64-cm thick scintillation counter.

x4codes.hlp: Indiana University, Bloomington, IN, United States of America

x4freetext: The measurements were performed by stopping pions in
aluminium near the target and detecting mu+ decays
between beam pulses of 1 microsecond duration.
The errors include both statistical errors
and uncertainties in target thickness.
Uncertainty of 9-12% in the
normalization of the experiment depending on the
thickness of the pion stopper used. For the heavier
targets the fluctuations in the cross sections for
the different final states are largely averaged out
in the inclusive cross sections. However, the cross
sections for mass < 20 are often dominated by a few
final states and exhibit strong variations for
different targets.
Measured cross section were corrected For Coulomb
barrier For pi+ mesons.
The energy above threshold of pion production.
